Star Trek: Phoenix
Deck 8: Senior Staff Quarters / cso-bjørge
Lt. JG. Rémy Salarda 06-Sep-20 09:19 AM
Cosek was packing his belongings. It was strange, he was visiting a conference on Earth during his shore leave, discussing the recently discovered ruins on an uninhabited planet. From watching some presentations on the previous discoveries and participating in some archeology workshops, his days at the conference were interesting and fun... Until he was approached by a small group of scientists, and one of the highest ranking members of starfleet science. They wanted him to be the station commander of the orbital research outpost, and head of the mission. He was humbled of course, but also overwhelmed, but sadly, the admiral gave him little time, he had even said that after watching Cosek at the conference, he took care of all the paperwork, he could be on a shuttle the same day.. Cosek said yes after talking to the group for some time. He knew all about the mission because of the conference, and this was basically what he had prepared for all this time: a large scientific excursion. And yet he had mixed feelings, as he would have to say goodbye to the Phoenix.. It was now time to say goodbye to his friends here, he beams all non-essential luggage to the shuttlebay, and walks of into the hallway with a large backpack, that included a small cage with Quackford at the top, as well as a trolley filled with gifts. (edited)

Lieutenant Sara Bjørge 14-Sep-20 01:16 AM
She hadn't been able to sleep. It wasn't as if she didn't desperately want to, but the mission still stung fresh in her mind. Everyone on the ship had made it back alive of course.. they'd lost Noah but in the grand scheme of things, as cruel as it felt, they'd been wildly lucky to have only lost one person. Though his screams of being eaten alive were haunting.. at least they hadn't had to see the body.. or whatever would've been left. She sat on her bed clad in shorts and a cropped pajama top, knees to her chin as she vaguely scrolled through the hookup app that Maggie had sent her. While Maggie may have sang it's graces, none of these guys were very interesting, and especially so that she had feelings for someone already.. But she either needed a heavy, heavy drink or some other flavor of distraction to not think about this every few minutes. Unhealthy coping? Who she? She bad? Looking up at the sound of her bell, she closed all the open windows and set her PADD face down. "Come in." (edited)

Lieutenant Sara Bjørge 27-Nov-20 07:03 PM
Waking up was a touch more difficult than she'd imagined. Gibs had decided the area between her throat and chest was the most comfortable spot in her entire room to sleep. Not counting his luxury cat bed, his cat box, his cat climber with a nest, or even his own pillow pile, no. It had to be her chest. He was, perhaps, getting a bit too comfortable being an inside cat..Spoiled rotten. Gently scooting him off onto his own pillow, he mewled in protest for a moment before huddling back into the divot he'd made and going back to sleep as Sara got up from bed with a soft cough and a deep breath of fresh air before she began her morning routine. Checking her PADD, there was already a roster of things to do, and she now apparently had an assistant! That was equally thrilling as the meeting that was due to happen in a few hours. She'd definitely be inviting her shiny new assistant to sit in on it to catch them up to speed. Shower, hair care, lotion, and she was done. She had been told that a lot of alien species were sensitive to the smell humans put off, so she always attempted to smell as good as she possibly could, making sure to wash and lather extremely well before smearing herself in a lotion that smelt..not too heavily, but pleasant. No need to be distracting. Almond or coconut was her go-to. Dressing and putting her long hair in it's traditional braid over the front of her shoulder, she gave herself a quick once over in the mirror, gave Gibs a kiss goodbye, and headed out the door.

They stayed that way for several hours, both having fallen asleep.
